Step 1. Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio.  
• Total Liabilities can be computed as:  
  Total Liabilities = Total Assets – Total Owner’s Equity  
  = 14534228.78 – 13905750.76  
  = 628478.02  

• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
  = 628478.02 / 14534228.78  
  ≈ 0.0433 → Rounded to 0.04  

Step 2. Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (1620560.42 / 2869560.42) × 100  
  ≈ 56.49%  

Step 3. Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio.  
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Total Current Liabilities  
  = -650630.22 / 628478.02  
  ≈ -1.0367 → Rounded to -1.04  

Thus, the result is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.04",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "56.49%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-1.04"
  }
}
